FIG. 1 shows one embodiment of the invention in which a hysteroscope has been inserted into a mammalian uterus;


FIG. 2 shows the embodiment of the invention shown in FIG. 1 and shows the distended uterine cavity after it has been expanded prior to delivery of the caustic paste;


FIG. 3 shows the embodiment of the invention shown in FIGS. 1 and 2 and shows a caustic composition being applied to the endometrial mucosa;


FIG. 4 shows the embodiment of the invention shown in FIGS. 1, 2 and 3 in which the neutralized caustic composition is flushed from the surface of the endometrium after treatment;


FIG. 5 shows another embodiment of the invention in which a catheter has been inserted into a mammalian uterus; and


FIG. 6 shows the embodiment of the invention shown in FIG. 5 after the uterine cavity has been expanded by the delivery of the caustic paste.
